}{}\begin{equation*} {\rm F1} - {\rm score} = \frac{{2 \times {\rm TP}}}{{2 \times {\rm TP} + {\rm FP} + {\rm FN}}} \end{equation*}\end{document}</tex-math></disp-formula></p>
      <p>Finally, if there were two redundant rules, only the one with higher F1-score was retained. The redundancy between two rules R<sub>1</sub> and R<sub>2</sub> was measured by the Jaccard index (JI) given by
